OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775113301
OL,3,CTwo migrants die crossing Channel as
OL,4,Coverall small boat journeys down by a
OL,5,Cthird
OL,7,FThe number of migrants who have
OL,8,Farrived in the UK after crossing the
OL,9,FEnglish Channel so far in 2026 is down
OL,10,Fby a third compared with the same
OL,11,Fperiod last year, figures show.
OL,13,FSome 4,441 migrants arrived in the
OL,14,Ffirst three months of 2026, according
OL,15,Fto the latest Home Office data.
OL,17,FThis is 33% lower than the number who
OL,18,Fhad reached the UK by this point in
OL,19,F2025, which was 6,642.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775113301
OL,3,CTwo migrants die crossing Channel as
OL,4,Coverall small boat journeys down by a
OL,5,Cthird
OL,7,FIt is also down 18% on the 5,435 who
OL,8,Farrived in the first three months of
OL,9,F2024.
OL,11,FThe sharp drop in arrivals so far in
OL,12,F2026 could be due partly to conditions
OL,13,Fin the English Channel, which have
OL,14,Fbeen more unsettled than in the early
OL,15,Fmonths of 2025.
OL,17,FA combination of low temperatures,
OL,18,Fpoor visibility, less daylight and
OL,19,Fstormy weather makes the journey
OL,20,Facross the Channel particularly
OL,21,Fdifficult.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775113301
OL,3,CTwo migrants die crossing Channel as
OL,4,Coverall small boat journeys down by a
OL,5,Cthird
OL,7,FThe latest Home Office Figures come on
OL,8,Fthe same day as two people are
OL,9,Freported to have died crossing the
OL,10,FChannel, with more hospitalised.
OL,12,FA deal between the UK and France was
OL,13,Falso set to expire at midnight on
OL,14,FWednesday morning but received a
OL,15,Ftemporary extension at the last minute
OL,16,Fwith an injection of extra funding
OL,17,Ffrom the Home Office.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775113301
OL,3,CTwo migrants die crossing Channel as
OL,4,Coverall small boat journeys down by a
OL,5,Cthird
OL,7,FThe existing near #500 million
OL,8,Farrangement was due to expire at
OL,9,Fmidnight on Wednesday morning, and saw
OL,10,FFrench authorities patrol beaches to
OL,11,Fstop migrants attempting to make the
OL,12,Fcrossing.
OL,14,FThe extension, which came with a
OL,15,Fpricer tag of #16.2 million in UK
OL,16,Ffunding, is designed to give both
OL,17,Fparties time to continue negotiations
OL,18,Fon a new deal.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775113301
OL,3,CTwo migrants die crossing Channel as
OL,4,Coverall small boat journeys down by a
OL,5,Cthird
OL,7,FIn a statement, the Home Office said:
OL,8,F"The Home Secretary is driving a hard
OL,9,Fbargain with the French to deliver the
OL,10,Fbest deal for the British people to
OL,11,Fprevent illegal migrants crossing the
OL,12,Fchannel. Essentially, getting more
OL,13,Fbang for our buck."
OL,15,FShabana Mahmood has previously been
OL,16,Funderstood to be pushing for the new
OL,17,Farrangement to include performance-
OL,18,Frelated clauses that would link
OL,19,Ffunding to the proportion of boats
OL,20,Fintercepted by the French, as first
OL,21,Freported by the Times.
OL,26,@pD@AOUuD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1775113301
OL,3,CTwo migrants die crossing Channel as
OL,4,Coverall small boat journeys down by a
OL,5,Cthird
OL,7,FThe Home Secretary said: "Our work
OL,8,Fwith France has stopped 42,000
OL,9,Fattempts by illegal migrants to make
OL,10,Fthe journey across the Channel.
OL,12,F"While we finalise a new and improved
OL,13,FUK-France deal, French law enforcement
OL,14,Foperations to stop illegal migrants in
OL,15,FFrance will continue.
OL,17,F"I will do whatever it takes to
OL,18,Frestore order and control at our
OL,19,Fborders."
OL,26,@oD@ZOUtD@AOUyD@AOU{D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
